<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN279">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>keṭuka cintai kaṭitiva ṭuṇivē</l>
<l>mūtiṉ makaḷi rāta ṟakumē</l>
<l>mēṉā ḷuṟṟa ceruviṟ kivaṭaṉṉai</l>
<l>yāṉai yeṟintu kaḷattoḻin taṉaṉē</l>
<l>neruna luṟṟa ceruviṟkivaḷ koḻunaṉ</l>
<l>perunirai vilaṅki yāṇṭu paṭṭaṉaṉē</l>
<l>yiṉṟuñ ceruppaṟai kēṭṭu viruppuṟṟu mayaṅki</l>
<l>vēṟkaik koṭuttu veḷituvirit tuṭīip</l>
<l>pāṟumayirk kuṭumi yeṇṇey nīvi</l>
<l>yorumaka ṉalla tillōḷ</l>
<l>cerumuka nōkkic celkaveṉa viṭumē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
  <l>  Let [my] mind be lost. Fierce is her determination.</l>
  <l>Becoming a [solitary] woman of an ancient house is befitting [to her].</l>
  <l>In the battle that took place the day before her brother</l>
  <l>stayed behind on the battle field, having attacked an elephant.</l>
  <l>In the battle that took place yesterday her husband</l>
  <l>fell there, having obstructed great rows [of enemies?].</l>
  <l>Today, too, hearing the battle drum, she is confused with longing,</l>
  <l>puts the spear in [his] hand, spreads something white and dresses [him] </l>
  <l>smearing [his] crest of scattered hair with sesame oil,</l>
  <l>she who has nothing but one son</l>
  <l>looks the battle in the face [and] sends [him] off: go!</l>
  </lg>
